wdi2-NV.MNF.MTRN.ZS.UN.def: Value added in manufacturing is the sum of gross output less the value of intermediate inputs used in production for industries classified in ISIC major division D. Machinery and transport equipment correspond to ISIC divisions 29, 30, 32, 34, and 35.
wdi2-NV.MNF.MTRN.ZS.UN.name: Machinery and transport equipment
wdi2-NV.MNF.MTRN.ZS.UN.source: United Nations Industrial Development Organization, International Yearbook of Industrial Statistics.
